title: Netherlands Inflation Rate MoM
description: The Consumer Price Index in Netherlands increased 1.10 percent in October of 2022 over the previous month. Inflation Rate MoM in Netherlands averaged 0.28 percent from 1960 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 4.40 percent in April of 1964 and a record low of -2.70 percent in July of 1962. Inflation Rate MoM measures month over month change in the price of goods and services. This page provides - Netherlands Inflation Rate MoM- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Statistics Netherlands
